<subSubSection id="C301653BFFA5FFF0FF36FA94FBD0FA0B" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA436B0FFA5FFF0FF36FA94FED9FAFE" blockId="11.[189,310,1326,1352]" box="[189,310,1326,1352]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<heading id="D0EC81DCFFA5FFF0FF36FA94FED9FAFE" bold="true" box="[189,310,1326,1352]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B96FEAA2FFA5FFF0FF36FA94FED9FAFE" bold="true" box="[189,310,1326,1352]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA436B0FFA5FFF0FF36FAE7FBD0FA0B" blockId="11.[189,1399,1373,1470]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D33FFA5FFF0FED1FAE4FE30FAC1" baseAuthorityName="Wickham" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[346,479,1373,1399]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pachystilicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hanhami">
<emphasis id="B96FEAA2FFA5FFF0FED1FAE4FE30FAC1" box="[346,479,1373,1399]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. hanhami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by longer and denser setae covering body, longitudinal carina of basisternum more elevated. Additionally, median emargination of posterior margin of sternite VIII is deeper and broader than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D33FFA5FFF0FEFDFA1EFE15FA0B" baseAuthorityName="Wickham" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[374,506,1443,1469]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pachystilicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hanhami">
<emphasis id="B96FEAA2FFA5FFF0FEFDFA1EFE15FA0B" box="[374,506,1443,1469]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. hanhami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, depth of emargination of ca ¼ of sternite length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
